WEBVTT

00:05:28.971 --> 00:05:32.433
was that there was
a dose-response relationship

00:05:32.433 --> 00:05:37.033
between ACEs and health outcomes:

00:05:37.033 --> 00:05:40.952
the higher your ACE score,
the worse your health outcomes.

00:05:40.952 --> 00:05:44.203
For a person with an ACE score
of four or more,

00:05:44.203 --> 00:05:47.895
their relative risk of chronic
obstructive pulmonary disease

00:05:47.895 --> 00:05:52.446
was two and a half times that
of someone with an ACE score of zero.

00:05:53.096 --> 00:05:56.370
For hepatitis, it was also
two and a half times.

00:05:56.370 --> 00:05:59.690
For depression, it was
four and a half times.

00:05:59.690 --> 00:06:03.123
For suicidality, it was 12 times.